name: Date and time
description: Internation standard format for date and time (ISO 8601): yyyy-mm-ddTHH:MM{TZ} where yyyy is 4 digit year, mm is month dd is day, HH is hour, MM is minute. The timezone format {TZ} is either "Z" for UTC or, for example, "-01:00" for one hour behind UTC

name: Longitude
description: Decimal longitude in degrees east

name: Latitude
description: Decimal latitude in degrees north

name: Temperature
description: Temperature in degrees C

name: Salinity
description: Practical Salinity

name: Fluoroesence
description: Fluoroescence

name: CDOM
description: Color Dissolved Organic Matter

name: Transmissivity
description: Transmissivity of seawater

name: Wind Speed
description: Wind speed

name: Wind Direction
description: Wind Direction - angle from true north that wind is coming from

name: Ship Heading
description: Direction the ship is pointing in relative to true north

name: Ship Pitch
description: Pitch of the ship from vertical

name: Ship Roll
description: Roll of the ship from vertical

name: Bottom Depth
description: Depth of the seafloor measured by CHIRP

name: Filename
description: Origin filename for data that takes in input datasets

name: First Filename
description: For time averaged data the first input file in the averaging window

name: Last Filename
description: For time averaged data the last input file in the averaging window

name: Station
description: ID for the station

name: East-west velocity
description: E-W Component of a velocity vector (+ve eastwards)

name: North-south velocity
description: N-S component of a velocity vector (+ve northwards)

name: Vertical velocity
description: Vertical velocity (+ve upwards)

name: Speed
description: Speed

name: Direction
description: Direction relative to true north (direction coming from)
